<p>My Query: </p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM TBL_TEST  WHERE MATCH(Name, Company, City, State) AGAINST ('++MyCity' IN BOOLEAN MODE); </code></pre>  <p>gives an expected </p>  <blockquote>   <p>SQL ERROR: <code>Error Code: 1064: syntax error, unexpected '+'</code></p> </blockquote>  <p><strong>My Question is</strong>: How can I pre-validate a search expression in my query. The search expression (here ++MyCity) is provided by my application users, and I want to let them know that the expression entered by them is wrong. </p>  <p>I want to minimize unnecessary db hits.</p>